from all of your individual apartments
and homes out there.

00:22:31.621 --> 00:22:33.748 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Ron Curzan is still with us,

00:22:33.748 --> 00:22:38.753 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and that is because we are going to have
a letter read from the class.

00:22:38.753 --> 00:22:42.882 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And since he already knows
how to pronounce the brother’s name,

00:22:43.841 --> 00:22:47.011 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’m going to let Ron introduce him again.

00:22:49.680 --> 00:22:53.392 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The class letter will be read
by Brother Phongsri.

00:22:55.811 --> 00:23:00.524 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“To the Governing Body and the Bethel family:

00:23:02.026 --> 00:23:06.113 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We were so excited
when we received our invitations

00:23:06.113 --> 00:23:10.034 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to attend the 149th class of Gilead.

00:23:10.034 --> 00:23:12.828 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“However, when it was announced

00:23:12.828 --> 00:23:17.166 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“that the 149th class would be postponed,

00:23:17.166 --> 00:23:20.127 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“anxiety filled our hearts

00:23:20.127 --> 00:23:23.506 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“as to what our future would be.

00:23:24.632 --> 00:23:27.927 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“To help in allaying this anxiety,

00:23:27.927 --> 00:23:31.389 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“the Governing Body made loving decisions

00:23:31.389 --> 00:23:33.391 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to comfort us.

00:23:33.391 --> 00:23:38.104 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We never felt abandoned or forgotten.

00:23:38.104 --> 00:23:42.483 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“One thing we were absolutely confident of

00:23:42.483 --> 00:23:47.238 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“was that the Governing Body
would do all they could

00:23:47.238 --> 00:23:49.949 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to make sure we had the class!

00:23:51.659 --> 00:23:55.746 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We are ever thankful for the Bethel family

00:23:55.746 --> 00:23:57.790 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“who warmly welcomed us

00:23:57.790 --> 00:24:00.376 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“into their hearts and their home.

00:24:01.294 --> 00:24:04.380 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“It seemed every day someone would ask:

00:24:04.380 --> 00:24:09.343 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘Do you need anything?’
or ‘How can I help you?’

00:24:09.343 --> 00:24:13.848 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We have observed this beautiful,
obedient Bethel family

00:24:13.848 --> 00:24:18.853 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and have learned a lot,
especially how to show personal interest

00:24:18.853 --> 00:24:23.149 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“in concrete ways during difficult times.

00:24:23.149 --> 00:24:26.444 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We can say that we had practical lessons

00:24:26.444 --> 00:24:29.739 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“in endurance, love,

00:24:29.739 --> 00:24:33.951 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“concern for others, trust in Jehovah,

00:24:33.951 --> 00:24:37.038 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“obedience, and shepherding.

00:24:37.997 --> 00:24:40.124 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“This is an example

00:24:40.124 --> 00:24:44.003 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“that we will take with us in our hearts

00:24:44.003 --> 00:24:48.632 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and try to reflect
in our dealings with others.

00:24:50.468 --> 00:24:55.306 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Once the school started, we could see
Jehovah’s hand in the arrangements

00:24:55.306 --> 00:24:59.935 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and how the brothers taking the lead
trusted in Jehovah

00:24:59.935 --> 00:25:03.898 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and the arrangements he had in place.

00:25:03.898 --> 00:25:06.734 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“As one of our first lessons,

00:25:06.734 --> 00:25:09.862 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“we want to follow their fine example

00:25:09.862 --> 00:25:12.740 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“in showing trust in Jehovah

00:25:12.740 --> 00:25:16.619 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“for whatever lies ahead.

00:25:16.619 --> 00:25:20.247 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We were touched by the sincerity

00:25:20.247 --> 00:25:24.460 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“of our instructors, ‘gifts in men,’

00:25:24.460 --> 00:25:28.464 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“who helped us to broaden and improve

00:25:28.464 --> 00:25:31.425 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“our understanding of the Scriptures.

00:25:33.135 --> 00:25:36.847 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“It is our heartfelt desire

00:25:36.847 --> 00:25:39.558 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to do as the psalmist sang

00:25:39.558 --> 00:25:43.771 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“at Psalm 105:1:

00:25:43.771 --> 00:25:46.982 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘Give thanks to Jehovah,

00:25:46.982 --> 00:25:49.151 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘call on his name,

00:25:49.151 --> 00:25:52.571 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“make his deeds known among the peoples!’

00:25:53.489 --> 00:25:58.202 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Yes, we want to share what we have learned

00:25:58.202 --> 00:26:00.329 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“with humble hearts,

00:26:00.329 --> 00:26:03.958 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“all to the praise of our Grand Instructor,

00:26:03.958 --> 00:26:06.001 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Jehovah God.

00:26:06.001 --> 00:26:10.965 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“More than that, we are determined
to use all that we have learned

00:26:10.965 --> 00:26:13.592 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to continue to grow spiritually

00:26:13.592 --> 00:26:18.597 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and be used in whatever way
Jehovah decides to use us.

00:26:21.225 --> 00:26:25.062 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“All that we experienced during our time here

00:26:25.062 --> 00:26:27.064 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“makes us appreciate

00:26:27.064 --> 00:26:31.152 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“our loving worldwide brotherhood
all the more

00:26:31.152 --> 00:26:34.447 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and continues to give us insight

00:26:34.447 --> 00:26:38.200 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“into what it will be like to live together

00:26:38.200 --> 00:26:40.911 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“in Jehovah’s new world.

00:26:40.911 --> 00:26:45.749 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We take all these memories
and lessons we learned here

00:26:45.749 --> 00:26:48.169 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“on to our assignments,

00:26:48.169 --> 00:26:50.963 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and we are determined

00:26:50.963 --> 00:26:54.133 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to follow your examples

00:26:54.133 --> 00:26:56.594 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“in bringing honor and glory

00:26:56.594 --> 00:26:59.597 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to our heavenly Father, Jehovah.

00:27:01.515 --> 00:27:04.059 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Your brothers and sisters,

00:27:04.059 --> 00:27:07.271 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the 149th Class of Gilead.”

00:27:09.607 --> 00:27:13.903 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Thank you for the beautiful sentiments
expressed in that class letter.

00:27:13.903 --> 00:27:16.572 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They were truly heartfelt.

00:27:18.199 --> 00:27:20.451 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I concluded my opening comments

00:27:20.451 --> 00:27:24.038 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with Deuteronomy 8:17, 18.

00:27:24.038 --> 00:27:28.834 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In part, it said:
“Remember that it is Jehovah your God

00:27:28.834 --> 00:27:31.378 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who gives power to you.”

00:27:32.546 --> 00:27:36.175 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You have had five months
of wonderful instruction.

00:27:36.175 --> 00:27:38.177 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You have learned so much

00:27:38.177 --> 00:27:41.639 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that you likely
did not fully appreciate before.

00:27:43.224 --> 00:27:47.520 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You have been elevated personally
by this experience.

00:27:47.520 --> 00:27:51.732 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It has improved your knowledge of God’s Word.

00:27:51.732 --> 00:27:55.402 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You may have already noticed
that your Christian personality

00:27:55.402 --> 00:27:59.698 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
has developed even further
than when you came.

00:27:59.698 --> 00:28:02.117 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But always remember:

00:28:02.117 --> 00:28:07.122 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The gifts you have attained
are not by your own power and strength.

00:28:09.291 --> 00:28:11.293 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Please find with me

00:28:11.293 --> 00:28:15.798 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Isaiah 40:29-31.

00:28:20.094 --> 00:28:22.471 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The thought of a source of power

00:28:22.471 --> 00:28:26.267 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is woven throughout the Scriptures.

00:28:26.267 --> 00:28:31.230 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Verse 28 is speaking about Jehovah,
the Creator of the ends of the earth.

00:28:32.273 --> 00:28:37.027 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But let’s now read chapter 40, verse 29:

00:28:37.027 --> 00:28:41.824 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
“He gives power to the tired one

00:28:41.824 --> 00:28:45.619 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
and full might to those lacking strength.”

00:28:47.413 --> 00:28:49.665 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’m old and tired.

00:28:51.041 --> 00:28:55.379 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Is Jehovah going to infuse me
with physical power and strength?

00:28:57.006 --> 00:29:00.593 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I wouldn’t complain if he chose to do so,

00:29:00.593 --> 00:29:04.930 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but that is not the kind of power
being discussed.

00:29:04.930 --> 00:29:08.100 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s not physical power.

00:29:08.100 --> 00:29:10.352 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, how do we know it isn’t?

00:29:10.352 --> 00:29:12.688 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Look at verse 30.

00:29:12.688 --> 00:29:16.942 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It says, even boys and young men
get tired physically.

00:29:16.942 --> 00:29:18.944 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Verse 30 says:

00:29:18.944 --> 00:29:23.574 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
“Boys will tire out and grow weary,

00:29:23.574 --> 00:29:26.994 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
and young men will stumble and fall.”

00:29:28.537 --> 00:29:30.581 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So then, what kind of power

00:29:30.581 --> 00:29:34.418 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
can we expect from Jehovah
according to these verses?

00:29:35.919 --> 00:29:40.341 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s power to reinvigorate us spiritually.

00:29:40.341 --> 00:29:44.386 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The power to help us carry out
our theocratic activities

00:29:44.386 --> 00:29:48.182 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to the extent our physical strength allows.

00:29:48.182 --> 00:29:52.603 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s the power to endure the trials of life.

00:29:52.603 --> 00:29:54.146 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, verse 31:

00:29:54.146 --> 00:29:57.066 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
“But those hoping in Jehovah

00:29:57.066 --> 00:29:59.234 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
“will regain power.

00:29:59.234 --> 00:30:02.780 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
“They will soar on wings like eagles.

00:30:02.780 --> 00:30:05.157 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
“They will run and not grow weary;

00:30:05.157 --> 00:30:08.369 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
they will walk and not tire out.”

00:30:10.621 --> 00:30:13.832 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In that verse, hope and power

00:30:13.832 --> 00:30:16.335 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
are linked together.

00:30:16.335 --> 00:30:20.130 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
By hoping in Jehovah
and depending on his strength,

00:30:20.130 --> 00:30:22.341 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we can soar like an eagle

00:30:22.341 --> 00:30:25.511 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
far above the challenges we face.

00:30:25.511 --> 00:30:28.555 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We can accomplish
the assignments we are given.

00:30:30.099 --> 00:30:32.976 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I wasn’t sure
if I could complete this assignment

00:30:32.976 --> 00:30:36.438 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
as the chairman of Gilead graduation.

00:30:36.438 --> 00:30:40.651 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But here we are
at the last part of the program.

00:30:40.651 --> 00:30:43.779 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Consider with me a final Scriptural thought

00:30:43.779 --> 00:30:46.365 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—Romans 15:13.

00:30:50.911 --> 00:30:55.290 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Here, too, hope and power
are linked together.

00:30:55.290 --> 00:30:58.836 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We can consider this as our prayer for you,

00:30:58.836 --> 00:31:03.382 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the 25 graduates of the 149th class.

00:31:04.299 --> 00:31:06.385 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Verse 13:

00:31:06.385 --> 00:31:10.973 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
“May the God who gives hope

00:31:10.973 --> 00:31:13.517 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
“fill you with all joy and peace

00:31:13.517 --> 00:31:15.978 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
“by your trusting in him,

00:31:15.978 --> 00:31:18.564 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
“so that you may abound in hope

00:31:18.564 --> 00:31:21.775 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
with power of holy spirit.”

00:31:24.361 --> 00:31:28.365 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Trust absolutely in Jehovah
and not in yourself.

00:31:28.365 --> 00:31:30.367 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If you do so, the verse said

00:31:30.367 --> 00:31:33.078 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
you will “abound in hope

00:31:33.078 --> 00:31:36.165 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with power of holy spirit.”

00:31:37.166 --> 00:31:41.503 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Holy spirit reminds us
of the fruitage of the spirit.

00:31:41.503 --> 00:31:43.505 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Make it a project to work

00:31:43.505 --> 00:31:47.885 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
on each of the nine aspects of the spirit

00:31:47.885 --> 00:31:52.556 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
mentioned in Galatians 5:22, 23.

00:31:54.683 --> 00:31:56.727 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We love all of you.

00:31:57.728 --> 00:32:01.231 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’m still open to Romans 15.

00:32:01.231 --> 00:32:03.442 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
My concluding comment to you

00:32:03.442 --> 00:32:07.446 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is in the 33rd verse:

00:32:07.446 --> 00:32:11.241 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
“May the God who gives peace

00:32:11.241 --> 00:32:13.786 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
“be with all of you.

00:32:13.786 --> 00:32:15.829 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
Amen.”

